<p style = "color: #993300; text-transform: uppercase;"> EXHIBITION CLASSES: </p>
<p> Puppy class (puppy) - from 6 to 9 months; </p>
<p> Junior class (junior) - from 9 to 18 months; </p>
<p> Intermediate class - from 15 to 24 months; </p>
<p> Open class (open) from 15 months; </p>
<p> Worker class (working) from 15 months; </p>
<p> The class of champions (champion) from 15 months; </p>
<p> Veteran class (veteran) since the age of 8. </p>
<p> The date for determining the age of the dog is the day before the start of the show. </p>
<p style = "color: #993300; text-transform: uppercase;"> EVALUATION AT THE EXHIBITION: </p>
<p> In the junior class, intermediate, open, working, champions and veterans, the following marks are awarded: </p>
<p> Excellent (excellent) - red ribbon; </p>
<p> Very good (very good) - blue ribbon; </p>
<p> Good (good) - green ribbon; </p>
<p> Satisfactory (satisfactory) - yellow ribbon; </p>
<p> Disqualification - white tape; </p>
<p> No evaluation. </p>
<p> In the puppy class, the following marks are awarded: </p>
<p> Very promising (very promising) - red ribbon; </p>
<p> Promising - blue ribbon; </p>
<p> Unpromising (no promising) - green ribbon. </p>


